Posted By: Brian McQueen

I have a group of 1909 Obaks I thought I'd offer up for trade to further some of my other projects.  Scans are available upon request. Some of these are pretty tough to come by....

Ort (Portland) SGC 40 - slight touches to corners/no creasing
Ragan (Oakland) SGC 40 - slight touches to corners/no creasing
Smith (LA) SGC AUT - no creasing/little wear
Williams (SF) SGC 30 - wrinkle in upper-left/little wear otherwise
Browning (SF) SGC 30 - might be nicest card in group - mostly sharp corners, little wear, no wrinkling or creasing
Ehman (SAC) SGC 30 - uncatalogued until recently, slight touches to corners/no creasing
McCreddie (Portland) SGC AUT - tough MGR card! no creasing/little wear
Ornsdorff (LA) SGC AUT - tiny wrinkle in corner, little wear

Below are some cards I need to further myself along on a few sets.  Thanks in advance!
